gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 127, Suns 112
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Jaylen Brown’s 37 points and five 3PM, the Celtics defeated the Suns, 127-112. Jayson Tatum (26 points, five rebounds, five assists) and Al Horford (24 points, three steals, six 3PM) added a combined 50 points in the victory. Devin Booker (23 points, seven assists), Bradley Beal (22 points, seven assists) and Kevin Durant (20 points) tallied 65 combined points for the Suns in the losing effort. The Celtics win their fourth consecutive game and improve to 52-14 on the season, while the Suns fall to 38-28.
